The paper is about a system for facilitating task design for reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of software primitives and a novel task design protocol, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The system is designed to be deployed in practical settings, which suggests that it may be relevant to Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of staged randomization to evaluate model capabilities, which could be relevant to Computer Vision (cs.CV).
